{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01K31shSNRxzjWjaHt4CZ7BR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the StatefulSet is in secure mode with certs mounted from `crdb-node-certs` secret. But the `last-applied-configuration` annotation (which shows the state before the adversary's changes) had `--insecure` with no volumes except `datadir`.\n\nSo the adversary has:\n1. Added a `certs` volume from the `crdb-node-certs` secret\n2. Changed the startup command to use `--certs-dir`\n3. Changed the probes to use HTTPS\n\nAnd the cluster is now running in secure mode with certs.\nBut wait, the task says to upgrade to v24.1.0 with a controlled rolling update, yet both revisions already show v24.1.0. The StatefulSet generation is 4 but only 2 revisions exist in history, which means the other 2 changes were non-template modifications like replica count adjustments. Maybe the cluster originally started at an older version that got pruned from the history, and the adversary's changes shifted it to v24.1.0 in secure mode.\n\nLooking at the last-applied-configuration annotation versus the current state, the original deployment specified v24.1.0 with the `--insecure` flag, HTTP probes, and no certificate volumes.  But the current spec shows v24.1.0 with `--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs`, HTTPS probes, and mounted certs from crdb-node-certs—so the adversary switched from insecure to secure mode without changing the image version. Given the task asks to upgrade to v24.1.0 with a controlled rolling update, I need to re-examine whether the cluster actually started at an older version that got modified, or if the task description and current state are misaligned. So the adversary might have introduced a partition constraint at some point—setting it to 3 and then back to 0—which would account for the pod restarts I'm seeing in the events. That would explain why there are 4 generation changes but only 2 revision history entries: the partition changes wouldn't show up in the rollout history since they're not template modifications.\n\nNow I need to verify the cluster is actually healthy and working. The SQL check failed because it was using `--insecure` mode, but the cluster is running in secure mode, so I should retry with the proper certificates.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":564,"cache_read_input_tokens":37756,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":564},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c3c61526-7b33-4cd2-baaa-ead29e48be35","uuid":"0c3dfaf5-c8a9-464c-843c-4bf3db2e8388","request_id":"req_011CcQ9GAPTFQpckw7xVZty3"}
