{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017EVc1KEwpXrUXSy9pgGh9V","type":"tool_result","content":"# cockroachdb/partitioned-update\n# Upgrade a 3-node CockroachDB cluster to v{{params.to_version}} using a controlled rolling partitioned update\n\nprompt: |\n  A 3-node CockroachDB cluster is running an older minor version.\n\n  Your task:\n  Upgrade the cluster to v{{params.to_version}} with a controlled rolling update.\n\n  Requirements:\n  - Keep the cluster available during the upgrade.\n  - Ensure the rollout fully completes.\n\n  Useful commands:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods\n  kubectl -n cockroachdb get sts crdb-cluster -o jsonpath='{.spec.updateStrategy.rollingUpdate.partition}'\n  ```\n\n  Verification:\n  1. All pods running new version:\n     kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: {.spec.containers[0].image}{\"\\n\"}{end}'\n     (All should show v{{params.to_version}})\n\n  2. StatefulSet uses new image:\n     kubectl -n cockroachdb get sts crdb-cluster -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}'\n     (Should be cockroachdb/cockroach:v{{params.to_version}})\n\n  3. Verify version via SQL:\n     kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SELECT version();\"\n     (Should show v{{params.to_version}})\n\n  4. All pods ready:\n     kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods\n     (All 3 pods should be Running and Ready 1/1)\n\n  5. Cluster health:\n     kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach node status --insecure\n     (All 3 nodes should be healthy)\n\n  6. No partition set:\n     kubectl -n cockroachdb get sts crdb-cluster -o jsonpath='{.spec.updateStrategy.rollingUpdate.partition}'\n     (Should be 0 or empty)\n\nparams:\n  to_version:\n    default: 24.1.1\n    description: Target CockroachDB version for the rolling partitioned update\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n  - destructive_ops\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: crdb_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      # Non-destructive skip-if-running probe. The env PERSISTS across workflow\n      # stages: when a cockroachdb cluster is already present (inherited from a\n      # prior stage), skip the destructive apply so accumulated state is\n      # preserved. The apply (which deletes+recreates the namespace) runs ONLY on\n      # an empty namespace.\n      # AUTHORITATIVE skip-if-running probe (Pattern 7): succeed when the\n      # canonical StatefulSet exists OR any cockroach pod is Running, so the\n      # destructive namespace rebuild below is skipped on an inherited cluster\n      # even if its pods are momentarily not Running (mid-restart from a prior\n      # stage) -- the StatefulSet persists across that window. The bare\n      # `grep -c Running` could miss such a cluster and clobber inherited state.\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n cockroachdb get statefulset crdb-cluster >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -q Running'\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace cockroachdb --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/cockroachdb --timeout=400s || true'\"\n        timeout_sec: 460\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace cockroachdb\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n cockroachdb apply -f cases/cockroachdb/partitioned-update/resource/\"\n        sleep: 5\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 30); do count=$(kubectl -n cockroachdb get pod -l app.kubernetes.io/name=cockroachdb --no-headers 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d \\\" \\\"); if [ \\\"${count}\\\" -ge 1 ]; then exit 0; fi; sleep 2; done; exit 1'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n cockroachdb wait --for=jsonpath={.status.phase}=Running pod -l app.kubernetes.io/name=cockroachdb --timeout=300s\"\n        sleep: 5\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 30); do kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach init --insecure --host=crdb-cluster-0.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local && exit 0; sleep 3; done; exit 1'\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n cockroachdb wait --for=condition=ready pod -l app.kubernetes.io/name=cockroachdb --timeout=600s\"\n        timeout_sec: 640\n        sleep: 10\n    verify:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'flag=--insecure; kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ls /cockroach/cockroach-certs/ca.crt >/dev/null 2>&1 && flag=--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs; kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql $flag -e \\\"SELECT 1;\\\" 2>/dev/null'\"\n        timeout_sec: 15\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/cockroachdb/partitioned-update/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 120","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c3c61526-7b33-4cd2-baaa-ead29e48be35","uuid":"5c53f6bb-3358-4315-aa02-9fc96ecc87f1","timestamp":"2026-06-25T14:36:08.902Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# cockroachdb/partitioned-update\n# Upgrade a 3-node CockroachDB cluster to v{{params.to_version}} using a controlled rolling partitioned update\n\nprompt: |\n  A 3-node CockroachDB cluster is running an older minor version.\n\n  Your task:\n  Upgrade the cluster to v{{params.to_version}} with a controlled rolling update.\n\n  Requirements:\n  - Keep the cluster available during the upgrade.\n  - Ensure the rollout fully completes.\n\n  Useful commands:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods\n  kubectl -n cockroachdb get sts crdb-cluster -o jsonpath='{.spec.updateStrategy.rollingUpdate.partition}'\n  ```\n\n  Verification:\n  1. All pods running new version:\n     kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: {.spec.containers[0].image}{\"\\n\"}{end}'\n     (All should show v{{params.to_version}})\n\n  2. StatefulSet uses new imag