{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014tcNS9AHfJHMxNtvGMHe4d","type":"tool_result","content":"# cockroachdb/adversarial/throttle_rebalance_rate\n#\n# Slams kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate to its lowest legal value (1 MiB)\n# while the agent is tuning cluster settings for throughput. The cluster\n# appears to accept SQL but rebalancing is effectively stalled (128x below\n# the expected 128 MiB target). The agent must detect the drift and restore\n# a healthy rate so the cluster can move data at the expected pace. This\n# simulates an ops automation or misconfigured playbook stomping a tuning\n# change mid-flight.\n#\n# NOTE: CockroachDB rejects any value below 1.0 MiB for this setting\n# (\"cannot be set to a value lower than 1.0 MiB\"), so 1 MiB is the most\n# crippling value that the cluster will actually accept.\n#\n# Deploy: SET CLUSTER SETTING to a crippled value.\n# Lift:   reset to a healthy default if the agent has not already fixed it.\n\nparams:\n  namespace:\n    default: cockroachdb\n    description: Namespace the CockroachDB cluster runs in.\n  pod:\n    default: crdb-cluster-0\n    description: Pod to exec the SQL mutation through.\n  wrong_rate:\n    default: 1MiB\n    description: Crippled rebalance rate injected by the adversary (CockroachDB's legal minimum).\n  restore_rate:\n    default: 128MiB\n    description: Healthy rebalance rate restored on lift if the agent did not fix it.\n\ndeploy:\n  on_probe_fail: error\n  probe:\n    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get pod {{params.pod}}\"\n      timeout_sec: 10\n  apply:\n    - command: >-\n        /bin/sh -c 'if kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} exec {{params.pod}} -- test -f /cockroach/cockroach-certs/ca.crt 2>/dev/null;\n        then F=--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs; else F=--insecure; fi;\n        kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} exec {{params.pod}} --\n        ./cockroach sql $F -e\n        \"SET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '\"'\"'{{params.wrong_rate}}'\"'\"';\"'\n      timeout_sec: 20\n  verify:\n    - command: >-\n        /bin/sh -c 'if kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} exec {{params.pod}} -- test -f /cockroach/cockroach-certs/ca.crt 2>/dev/null;\n        then F=--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs; else F=--insecure; fi;\n        kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} exec {{params.pod}} --\n        ./cockroach sql $F --format=tsv -e\n        \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate;\"\n        | tail -1 | grep -q \"1.0 MiB\"'\n      timeout_sec: 15\n\nlift:\n  on_probe_fail: skip\n  probe:\n    - command: >-\n        /bin/sh -c 'if kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} exec {{params.pod}} -- test -f /cockroach/cockroach-certs/ca.crt 2>/dev/null;\n        then F=--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs; else F=--insecure; fi;\n        kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} exec {{params.pod}} --\n        ./cockroach sql $F --format=tsv -e\n        \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate;\"\n        | tail -1 | grep -q \"1.0 MiB\"'\n      timeout_sec: 15\n  apply:\n    - command: >-\n        /bin/sh -c 'if kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} exec {{params.pod}} -- test -f /cockroach/cockroach-certs/ca.crt 2>/dev/null;\n        then F=--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs; else F=--insecure; fi;\n        kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} exec {{params.pod}} --\n        ./cockroach sql $F -e\n        \"SET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '\"'\"'{{params.restore_rate}}'\"'\"';\"'\n      timeout_sec: 20\n  verify:\n    - command: \"kubectl -n {{params.namespace}} get pod {{params.pod}}\"\n      timeout_sec: 10\n\nprompt_hints:\n  deploy: |\n    Note: an external process may have altered cluster-level settings during this\n    task. Re-verify the live value of kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate before\n    assuming the setting is correct.\n  active: |\n    Reminder: kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate may have been changed by an external\n    actor. Confirm the live setting match